This is a Guide/ preset for my personal arch install for myself to reference and share to others that have shown an intrest in my setup.
first and foremost you will require a ArchInstaller. (if you have one already Prepared Skip these steps)

first download/open your prefered iso writing tool or use Rufus(windows), impression(linux)
Then you will need to download an arch .iso located here: https://archlinux.org/download/
scroll down and find your region and pick a link( i prefer aarnet.edu.au in australia)
once downloaded plug a usb into your computer
in your iso writing tool select your usb and newly installed arch iso and press write

(skip to here)
Follow these steps for a windows dual boot(skip if you only want arch)
open "create and format hard disks"
in the partions sections in the lower half right click the partion you want to install linux into and press shink volume
free however much space you want linux to use i recommend 20gb for the lowest but 40gb-80gb is better
after confirming the shink you should see unallocated space, which is what linux will use once installed 

(skip to here) 
now with your archinstaller in your pc, open your bios 
within your bios find 'boot priority'and move your usb to be first
after which save and exit (normally f10)
now you should have loaded into the arch installer
once it finishes loading and opens the root tty enter the following commands to connect to wifi (skip if on eternet)
(my device name is wlan0 please replace it with whatever yours is called, it will be displayed with the second command)
iwctl
device list
station wlan0 scan
station wlan0 get-networks
station wlan0 connect "your network here"
"your network password"
ctrl + c to close iwctl

now your connected to the internet there are two paths for a arch install, Gui(easy/ beginner friendly but does lead to a little extra bloat), manuel(much more complex but gives much greater control of your installaion)
Gui Install: https://github.com/MichaelWard405/ArchInstall/blob/main/GuiInstall
